title.12: Hercules: Prince of Power: Full Circle (1989)
title.38: Conan of the Isles Graphic Novel (1988) #1
title.95: Cloak and Dagger: Predator and Prey (1988)

description.0: Phillips and his delegates help a Marine pilot escape death.
description.1: Supposedly, Franz Kraus hired Silver Sable to test a security system. But when Kraus turns out to be a neo-Nazi, Spider-Man smells a rat!
description.2: Out of love for Marrina, Namor attempts to reason with the Leviathan-beast she has become. Although touched by Namor's feelings, the Avengers decide to step in. Dr. Druid is now haunted by the "woman of his dreams" during the day.
description.3: The Black Panther's got a gift for the new Cap: a new shield! And when Cap uses the shield to go after the guys invading the Serpent Society's headquarters, well, everybody had better watch out!
description.5: The Power Pack meets Rebecca Littlehale! Who is this young teleporter and what is the source of her remarkable power?
description.6: Hawkeye, Silver Sable, and Sandman take down the Bartovian Liberation Front… in an airport!
description.10: Presenting a pulse-pounding adventure from the team who brought you the Silver Surfer back in the ‘60’s! It’s the Surfer vs. Mephisto! Mephisto vs. Galactus! And it looks like the Silver Surfer will finally surrender his soul to Mephisto!
description.11: What if Iron Man was a traitor? We may know Iron Man as one of the founding Avengers, but witness a world where Iron Man becomes a Judas to all of Earth’s heroes!
description.12: On the planet Wilamean, Hercules' revelry binge is cut short by the arrival of Galactus! Then, Herc's fallen son Arimathes challenges his absent father to a blood match!
description.13: The WC Avengers are off in the Grand Canyon - and in battle with the giant YETRIGAR! But there's more to this encounter than meets the eye…just what is Mockingbird up to?
description.17: Maddie gives birth, and the STAR CHILD is born! The child is born with some of dad's powers, and even some strange new abilities of its own!
description.18: Spider-Man is finally able to chase down Tarantula. And it looks like this case is all webbed up! But unbeknownst to the wall-crawler, Tarantula has a shocking new ally - Captain America!
description.19: Silver Surfer and Nova team-up! Will these two cosmic wanderers ever find The Contemplator? Nenora has usurped control over the Kree following the Supreme Intelligence’s meltdown. Plus, attack of the space pirates!
description.20: The First Appearance of Typhoid Mary!  Kingpin makes an offer to Typhoid she can't refuse after she bests Kingpin at his own game. Can Typhoid inspire love from any man? Even one with an iron will? And what happens when Matt Murdock meets Mary?
description.21: The Leader lets Betty Ross go, but he sends 3 giant robots to escort her back to the Hulk. Smashing time!
description.22: Illyana has a dream that feels more like a prophetic vision, setting her on the course to gain answers from Forge about the X-Men's demise.
description.23: Thor tries to live a peaceful life on Earth anew, but before he can begin, he is ambushed by the ferocious villain Mongoose! Good thing his Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man is around to lend a hand!
description.25: After seizing Apocalypse's warship, the team re-fits the vessel for their own means…while avoiding its many deathtraps!
description.27: The Fantastic Four plunge ever deeper into the Earth's depths, only to find themselves going up against the dark sorcerer known as Belasco! What plans does he have for Crystal?
description.28: After the Reavers run a murderous bank robbery, the X-Men ambush them to put a stop to their criminal ways.
description.29: Trying to absorb life force energy from the X-Man Storm, Karl Lykos has transformed once more into Sauron!
description.33: The First Full Appearance of Venom! Witness the return of Eddie Brock! And red-and-blue Spider-Man! Are Eddie and the symbiote still holding an irrational grudge against the wall-crawler? This is a Venom/Spider-Man smackdown you won’t want to miss!
description.34: How did Marrina transform into a Leviathan-like beast and what does this mean for the Avengers? Plus, a strange woman haunts Dr. Druid's dreams.
description.35: Now that iron Man has turned renegade, the Captain has decided to bring him in - but his old friend and ally isn't coming quietly! Meanwhile, the world meets the new Captain America's partner, Battle Star! And as if that weren't enough, an all-out war is breaking out within the sinister Serpent Society!
description.36: Lt. Alarnick has gone off the rails! And the object of his fury may be an innocent farming village!
description.37: Hawkeye must stop the dastardly Red Skull from launching a nuclear attack!  Plus, the Falcon takes flight in solo action!
description.40: There's a new Tarantula in town, and he's on a mission to take out any political refugee he can find!
description.41: The Elders pay for their insurrection, and Galactus feasts. On Kree-Lar, infighting between Skrulls establishes the leadership of an entire alien race. Death comes for Galactus. Is it coming for all of Zenn-La too?
description.42: The return of ARKON! But wait - wasn't Arkon just a movie character from Wonder Man's acting career? Not anymore, and his next target is the West Coast Avengers! Plus: to kill a Mockingbird!
description.48: Following their battle with Magneto, Phoenix and Beast seem to be the only survivors left of the X-Men!
description.49: Christmastime settles over New York City, and Daredevil and Kingpin celebrate in two very different worlds. A holiday-themed issue brought to you by master scribe Ann Nocenti and Marvel legend John Romita Jr.!
description.50: With most of his energy sapped, Hulk must battle Half-Life!
description.51: While en route to Magma's birthplace Nova Roma, Magma and Empath crash land and have only each other for support. While adventuring together, Amara discovers that she does have feelings for Manuel…
description.52: Thor returns to Earth and reunites with an old friend--Steve Rogers, now called simply "The Captain"! But when the two are attacked by the Demons of Death, there's a surprising twist of who is worthy to lift Mjolnir!
description.54: A slice-of-life holiday issue! X-Factor enjoys the Christmas season, and even Apocalypse gets in on the merriment!
description.56: To try and change Ms. Marvel back from a She-Thing, the FF go underground to find an old enemy-turned-friend- the Mole Man!
description.57: The bounty hunter O.Z. Chase goes over the last letter he received from Allison Blaire, detailing the experiences of the now-dead X-Men...
description.62: The First Cameo Appearance of Venom!   Spider-Man must rescue Chance from the merciless white-collar survivalists known as the Life Foundation! And that's just the beginning! Revealed at last- the astonishing identity of the super-villain who can slip past Spidey's spider sense! The second you see him, you'll know why!
description.63: Now that the Super-Adaptoid has acquired the powers of the Cosmic Cube, it is able to hold the Avengers captive. Can Captain America defeat the A.I menace?
description.64: Talk about guest-stars - this issue's got them! And the Captain's going to need all the help he can get from D-Man, Falcon, and Nomad because he's facing Mr. Hyde, Titania, Vibro, the Griffin, Armadillo, and the Captain's friend, Iron Man!
description.66: Watch out Viet Cong! Lt. Alarnick's new men are ready to serve...but why does Sgt. Little fear the Lt. has gone too far?
description.67: He's got all the powers of the West Coast Avengers - and he's not the Super-Adaptoid! The question isn't how the West Coast Avengers will beat him, but how will they survive the battle?
description.73: Ken Connell as Star Brand battles the Old Man once more at a Pittsburgh comic convention, but at a horrible cost! Star Brand knows there's only one way to fix things, and it isn't going to be pretty…
description.74: The Elders of the Universe need all the Infinity Gems for their takedown of Galactus- too bad the Soul Gem is safe in Surfer’s possession! Will Norrin relinquish the Soul Gem for the freedom of Shalla Bal and Mantis? Nova guest-stars!
description.75: New York is blacked out! It's up to Daredevil and Black Widow protect the innocent from the Horsemen of Apocalypse and gun-toting gang members!
description.76: The Hulk must defend his friends from the Savage Bull!
description.77: Thor strikes a victorious blow against the Celestials, but at a heavy cost--Mjolnir lies shattered. How will Thor carry on without his most powerful and reliable ally?
description.81: FALL OF THE MUTANTS tie-in! The Fantastic Four must team-up with their arch nemesis Dr. Doom! Will they really help him reclaim the Latverian throne? Guest-starring X-Factor!
description.84: With the X-Men all prisoner in his Antarctic base, Magneto renews his acts of terror on the human world!
description.89: Vietnamese villagers assault Sergeant Prikow's division!
description.90: The Witness comes to Pittsburgh, where a confrontation with Ken Connell leads to disastrous consequences! And when Spitfire arrives on the scene, what trouble will she find waiting for her there?
description.91: Put together an arms shipment, terrorists, and the high-rolling mercenary called Chance, and what have you got? You've got pretty big trouble for everyone's favorite wall-crawler in "Chance Encounter"!
description.92: Heavy Metal (Machine Man, Sentry 459, and Tess-One), are led by the Super-Adaptoid during an attack on the Avengers' Hydrobase.
description.93: FALL OF THE MUTANTS tie-in! The Captain and his allies are confronted by Famine, Horseman of Apocalypse!
description.94: Hawkeye is framed for murder!  Can he escape incarceration and prove his innocence? Plus, the Black Knight versus the Last Knight!
description.98: Absorbed into the hive mind of the Supreme Intelligence, Silver Surfer sees a reality never destined to be. Love, companionship, the blissfulness of peace- will Norrin Radd ever experience these things again? Back on Zenn-La, Shalla Bal’s in dire straits…and Mantis is nowhere to be found!
description.99: Moon Knight is hot on the trail of the sinister Cornelius Van Lunt - but considering that Van Lunt is Taurus of the late great Zodiac cartel, Moon Knight may find more than he bargained for!

4.text: For years, Nick Fury has led S.H.I.E.L.D. But the spy network has become corrupt and Fury's got to go underground to fight it... even though it means fighting— and killing— some of his closest friends as well!

6.text: Hawkeye, Silver Sable, and Sandman take down the Bartovian Liberation Front… in an airport!

7.text: Separated from the rest of the team, the last of the first generation Morituri has a baby! But can she singlehandedly defend her child from the alien Horde? And even if she does, can she survive the effects of her own powers?

8.text: The Punisher burns the metaphorical candle at both ends -- not only is he shaking down insider trading on Wall Street, but he’s also got his hands full with an indiscriminate killer! Who is the Skid Row Slasher?

12.text: On the planet Wilamean, Hercules' revelry binge is cut short by the arrival of Galactus! Then, Herc's fallen son Arimathes challenges his absent father to a blood match!

13.text: The WC Avengers are off in the Grand Canyon - and in battle with the giant YETRIGAR! But there's more to this encounter than meets the eye…just what is Mockingbird up to?

16.text: Unwilling to ignore Iron Man's crimes any longer, the government tasks the armored warrior, Firepower, to take down the former hero! And Firepower just might win! As Jim Rhodes looks on helplessly, Tony Stark takes the beating of his life! Is this the end of Iron Man?

17.text: Maddie gives birth, and the STAR CHILD is born! The child is born with some of dad's powers, and even some strange new abilities of its own!

18.text: Spider-Man is finally able to chase down Tarantula. And it looks like this case is all webbed up! But unbeknownst to the wall-crawler, Tarantula has a shocking new ally - Captain America!

19.text: Silver Surfer and Nova team-up! Will these two cosmic wanderers ever find The Contemplator? Nenora has usurped control over the Kree following the Supreme Intelligence’s meltdown. Plus, attack of the space pirates!

25.text: X-Factor fights and frees Apocalypse's sentient ship from its former master's control!

30.text: It's one thing to know that your super powers will kill you someday. But as the Morituri's Scatterbrain learns, it's another thing entirely to have death stare you in the face!

31.text: Frank Castle gets his hands dirty on Wall Street! Arnold Ansen doesn’t stand a chance...

33.text: The First Full Appearance of Venom! Witness the return of Eddie Brock! And red-and-blue Spider-Man! Are Eddie and the symbiote still holding an irrational grudge against the wall-crawler? This is a Venom/Spider-Man smackdown you won’t want to miss!
Artist Todd McFarlane used some design tweaks to make the backround fall back, bringing the black-suited, iconic image of Spider-Man to the forefront in one of his boldest drawings ever.

39.text: Iron Man is kicked out of the Avengers! When Tony Stark's quest to reclaim his technology takes him to Siberia, the Crimson Dynamo and the Titanium Man wait to defeat him once and for all! See Stark unveil a new all-black armor for a special mission that could leave Iron Man a murderer!

40.text: There's a new Tarantula in town, and he's on a mission to take out any political refugee he can find!

41.text: The Elders pay for their insurrection, and Galactus feasts. On Kree-Lar, infighting between Skrulls establishes the leadership of an entire alien race. Death comes for Galactus. Is it coming for all of Zenn-La too?

42.text: The return of ARKON! But wait - wasn't Arkon just a movie character from Wonder Man's acting career? Not anymore, and his next target is the West Coast Avengers! Plus: to kill a Mockingbird!

43.text: Here be Dragons! The Warriors Three are caught up in a dreamscape illusion while trying to recover a missing Asgardian! And Loki’s to blame!

53.text: A serial slasher is targeting young models in Manhattan -- can Spider-Man put a stop to it before Mary Jane's best friend becomes his next victim?

58.text: It's an archery duel to the death between Hawkeye and Trick Shot! Silver Sable's trying to save Hawkeye from the duel, because she knows that Trick Shot has made sure there's no way Hawkeye can win!

60.text: Is the government betraying the Morituri heroes they created? Strikeforce: Morituri discovers that the truth behind the government's stonewalling is even more devastating! Not only is the government secretly creating a new Morituri base, they plan to populate it with a new generation of Morituri warriors! Trouble is, this new Morituri-making process "Breeds Monsters"!

65.text: The X-Terminators, Artie, and Leech are being held prisoner by N'astirh as demons pour into Manhattan in full force. Can the X-Terminators escape in time to stave off the demonic horde?
The X-Terminators, Artie, and Leech are being held prisoner by N'astirh as demons pour into Manhattan in full force. Can the X-Terminators escape in time to stave off the demonic horde?

67.text: He's got all the powers of the West Coast Avengers - and he's not the Super-Adaptoid! The question isn't how the West Coast Avengers will beat him, but how will they survive the battle?

71.text: Iron Man vs. the Captain! Tony Stark vs. Steve Rogers! More determined than ever to reclaim his technology, Iron Man -- with help from Jim Rhodes -- breaks into the Vault and disarms the Guardsmen, causing a mass super villain breakout! Surely Stark wouldn't fight his oldest friend just to meet his own goals?

72.text: The New Mutants cope with the loss of Doug Ramsey. Magneto lashes out at his students for their carelessness, and Illyana responds in kind for his lack of concern. But with the X-Men gone too, is it up to the New Mutants to save the world now?

73.text: Ken Connell as Star Brand battles the Old Man once more at a Pittsburgh comic convention, but at a horrible cost! Star Brand knows there's only one way to fix things, and it isn't going to be pretty…

74.text: The Elders of the Universe need all the Infinity Gems for their takedown of Galactus- too bad the Soul Gem is safe in Surfer’s possession! Will Norrin relinquish the Soul Gem for the freedom of Shalla Bal and Mantis? Nova guest-stars!

79.text: X-Factor finally receives a hero’s welcome after saving the entire city from Apocalypse’s Horsemen.

82.text: The X-Men must fight their way through a demonic distortion of the Vietnam War in order to reach their final showdown with the Adversary! Colossus returns to help his former teammates, but will that be enough?

83.text: Spidey's final showdown with Sin Eater!

85.text: Where would you expect to find a showdown between Morituri and their alien foes, the Horde? Would you believe an Old West ghost town?

86.text: A plutonium sale could spell absolute disaster for Times Square, as Punisher races against the clock to neutralize a terrorist plot between ex-CIA and a pair of radicals.

88.text: The X-Terminators must battle their way through a veritable legion of demons to find the location of Artie, Leech, and Taki.
The X-Terminators must battle their way through a veritable legion of demons to find the location of Artie, Leech, and Taki.

95.text: When Cloak finds a killer parasite residing in his cloak, it will be up to the duo to stop them when it attaches itself to a legendary killer!

96.text: Justin Hammer has access to Tony Stark's technology, and Iron Man won't stand for it! But Tony is losing allies right and left -- with the police, S.H.I.E.L.D. and the Avengers all determined to stop him! When Iron Man battles the government-sponsored Mandroids, the Captain (Steve Rogers, the once and future Captain America) steps in to talk some sense into Stark!

97.text: With the Animator's Animates and Cameron Hodge's army attacking them on all fronts, the island of Paradise may be the final battleground for one New Mutant!

98.text: Absorbed into the hive mind of the Supreme Intelligence, Silver Surfer sees a reality never destined to be. Love, companionship, the blissfulness of peace- will Norrin Radd ever experience these things again? Back on Zenn-La, Shalla Bal’s in dire straits…and Mantis is nowhere to be found!

99.text: Moon Knight is hot on the trail of the sinister Cornelius Van Lunt - but considering that Van Lunt is Taurus of the late great Zodiac cartel, Moon Knight may find more than he bargained for!
